1.  First loging in to the remote server via ssh

        $ ssh bandit18@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
		  username: bandit18
		  password: kfBf3eYk5BPBRzwjqutbbfE887SVc5Yd 

	
2.	As soon as you try to login, you see visiting banner and - 
	
		...
		Enjoy your stay!

		Byebye !
		Connection to bandit.labs.overthewire.org closed.


3.	As the admin says -
			"The password for the next level is stored in a file readme in the homedirectory. 
			Unfortunately, someone has modified .bashrc to log you out when you log in with SSH. "



4.	Simply execute the commands on remote server without remaining logged in.

		$ ssh bandit18@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220 "cat readme"
		This is a OverTheWire game server. More information on http://www.overthewire.org/wargames
		bandit18@bandit.labs.overthewire.org's password: 
		IueksS7Ubh8G3DCwVzrTd8rAVOwq3M5x

	
~>	Here we got the passkey for the next level(19) "IueksS7Ubh8G3DCwVzrTd8rAVOwq3M5x"	

